    "Although S col.1 shows some variability, the average score remains high, indicating that even when the input contains colloquial speech, the system can effectively extract service names that capture the essence of the user's statements without significant loss in quality.",
    "An analysis of the causes of generation failures also revealed that colloquial speech itself is rarely a direct cause of failure.",
    "Additionally, the variety of generated service names demonstrates that the system successfully interprets the finer details of user intent, producing original and appropriate names.",
